[2;36m                    [0m         [33mtid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x000056487bd01580[0m[39m [0m[33mnid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x20[0m[39m waiting on condition  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNI global refs: [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m, weak refs: [0m[1;36m0[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA timeout error occurred during fuzzing operations, indicating that the main thread[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecame unresponsive while processing a PDF document. The thread was stuck in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Lexer.readToken` method for approximately [0m[1;36m28.61[0m[39m seconds, consuming over [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseconds of CPU time before triggering libFuzzer's timeout mechanism.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue manifests as a libFuzzer timeout error with the main thread entering a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRUNNABLE state but making no progress. The thread dump captured on [0m[1;36m2026[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m01[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m08:27:47[0m[39m shows the JVM was running with [0m[1;36m15[0m[39m active threads, with the main thread [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mthread #[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m being the problematic one.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Thread State Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe main thread was in a RUNNABLE state but appears to be stuck in an infinite or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextremely long-running loop. The thread consumed [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m660.[0m[39m43ms of CPU time over an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melapsed time of [0m[1;36m28.61[0m[39m seconds, indicating continuous CPU activity without [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompletion. The stack trace shows the execution path at the time of timeout.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Execution Path[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe call stack reveals the following execution flow:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Entry point through the fuzzer harness: [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. PDF text extraction: `PDFTextStripper.getText` and related methods[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. PDF content stream processing: `PDFStreamEngine.processPage` and operator [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Font loading and parsing: `PDType1Font.<init>` and `Type1Font.createWithPFB`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Type1 font parsing: `Type1Parser.parse` and `Type1Parser.parseBinary`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Lexical analysis: `Type1Lexer.nextToken` and `Type1Lexer.readToken`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Native instrumentation: `TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe thread was stuck at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m in `Type1Lexer.readToken` when the native method [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`traceConstCmpInt` was being called for instrumentation purposes.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Location of Hang**: The execution appears to be stuck in the Type1 font [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlexer's token reading logic, specifically at `Type1Lexer.readToken` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Native Method Involvement**: The immediate caller in the stack trace is a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnative method used for fuzzing instrumentation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`traceConstCmpInt`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is part [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the Jazzer fuzzing framework's data flow tracing.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Font Parsing Context**: The hang occurs during Type1 font parsing within the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext of PDF processing, specifically when creating a Type1Font from PFB [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPrinter[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFont Binary[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m format data.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Resource Consumption**: The high CPU usage [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m26[0m[39m+ seconds of CPU time[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m suggests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man active computational loop rather than a blocking I/O operation or deadlock.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **PDF Processing Chain**: The issue originated from attempting to extract text [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom a PDF document, which required loading and processing a Type1 font embedded in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor referenced by the document.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a comprehensive understanding of this timeout issue, the following [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents of the codebase should be investigated:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.readToken** [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The primary [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuspect where the hang occurred. Investigation should focus on:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m and surrounding code[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Loop conditions and termination criteria[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Input validation and boundary checks[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Handling of malformed or adversarial input data[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.nextToken** [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The method [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling readToken, which may provide context about token processing logic.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Type1Parser.parseBinary** [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The binary [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing logic that drives the lexer, particularly around line [0m[1;36m643[0m[39m.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Type1Parser.parse** [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The main parsing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point that should be examined for input validation and error handling.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Type1Font.createWithPFB** [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Font[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The font [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreation method that initiates parsing, which may need input sanitization.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Input Data Characteristics**: Understanding what characteristics of the fuzzed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput triggered this behavior would be valuable for reproducing and fixing the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Classification[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue represents a potential **Denial of Service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** vulnerability through[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malgorithmic complexity or infinite loop exploitation. An attacker could craft a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious PDF file with a specially formatted Type1 font that causes the parser to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menter a long-running or infinite loop, leading to resource exhaustion and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplication unresponsiveness.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs in `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` due to an infinite loop when [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing malformed font data containing excessive consecutive whitespace or NULL [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes. The root cause is the do-while loop structure at lines [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m247[0m[39m:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The outer `do-while` loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continues while `skip` is true[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The inner `while` loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m123[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m processes buffer contents[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. When whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m199[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or NULL bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m204[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are encountered, `skip` is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset to true[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The `[0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` condition at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m causes the outer loop to restart[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. The inner loop continues processing the same whitespace/NULL characters[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. This creates an infinite loop when the buffer contains only these characters[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer crafted input with a large sequence of whitespace or NULL bytes, causing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis algorithmic complexity vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Add Consecutive Skip Counter in [0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Approach**: Implement a counter-based protection similar to the pattern in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readStringNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1450[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1454[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m which limits excessive [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation Steps**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Define a constant for the maximum consecutive skips** [0m[1;39m([0m[39madd near line [0m[1;36m52[0m[39m with [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a constant like `private static final int MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS = [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m;`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This value is large enough for legitimate fonts with reasonable whitespace but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall enough to catch malicious input before timeout[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This aligns with BaseParser's protection pattern using MAX_LENGTH_LONG[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Add a skip counter in [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat line [0m[1;36m118[0m[39m, before the do-while loop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Initialize `int consecutiveSkips = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` before line [0m[1;36m119[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Increment and check the counter when skip is set** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat lines [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m204[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After `skip = true;` at line [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m, increment the counter[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After `skip = true;` at line [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m, increment the counter[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check if `consecutiveSkips > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If exceeded, throw `DamagedFontException` with a descriptive message including[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer position[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Reset counter when non-skip processing occurs**:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When any token is successfully returned [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall return statements in lines [0m[1;36m135[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m148[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m152[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m156[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m174[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m180[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m188[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m194[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m214[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m232[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m241[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the method exits [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormally[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When `skip` is false at the start of the do-while iteration, ensure the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounter remains at its current value [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdon't reset[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The counter should only be reset if we successfully process a meaningful token[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mwhich would return from the method[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Error message format**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follow the existing pattern from lines [0m[1;36m164[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m223[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Message: `[0m[32m"Excessive whitespace or NULL bytes at position "[0m[39m + [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This aligns with the existing DamagedFontException usage pattern in the file[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Detailed Implementation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix should modify the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method as follows:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate Token [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken prevToken[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    boolean skip;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    int consecutiveSkips = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add counter[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    do[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        skip = false;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            char c = [0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m existing delimiter checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m196[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCharacter.isWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                skip = true;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                consecutiveSkips++;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Increment counter[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkips > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        [0m[32m"Excessive whitespace or NULL bytes at position "[0m[39m + [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"NULL byte in font, skipped"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                skip = true;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                consecutiveSkips++;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Increment counter[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkips > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        [0m[32m"Excessive whitespace or NULL bytes at position "[0m[39m + [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m rest of the method [0m[33m...[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return null;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Fix is Optimal[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Preserves existing functionality**: The fix only adds protection against [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious input without changing the lexer's normal behavior. Legitimate fonts with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreasonable whitespace will parse correctly.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Follows established patterns**: [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mirrors `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readStringNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` protection pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1450[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1454[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses existing `DamagedFontException` with position information [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m164[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Aligns with CFFParser validation patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m263[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m269[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m293[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m296[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal invasiveness**: The fix only modifies the problematic method without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffecting other lexer methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tryReadNumber`, `readRegular`, `readComment`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readString`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m which already have safe loop patterns.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Appropriate threshold**: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive skips allows for legitimate font [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles with spacing while catching malicious input before timeout. This is similar [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min spirit to BaseParser's MAX_LENGTH_LONG [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m19[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for number parsing.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear error reporting**: The DamagedFontException includes buffer position, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelping with debugging and following the existing error pattern in the codebase.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No impact on tests**: The existing Type1LexerTest tests [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m43[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m135[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to pass as they use normal input. The fix prevents the timeout scenario [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout breaking valid use cases.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Legitimate fonts with excessive whitespace**: Extremely unlikely, but if a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid font has >[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive whitespace characters, it would be rejected.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The threshold of [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m is very conservative; legitimate fonts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdon't have such sequences[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If needed, the constant can be adjusted based on real-world font analysis[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Error handling upstream**: Code calling Type1Parser may need to handle [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDamagedFontException gracefully.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Already handled**: PDType1Font constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m227[0m[39m in the stack trace[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready has try-catch for IOException, which DamagedFontException extends[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PDFontFactory.createFont and related code already handle font loading errors [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgracefully[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance impact**: Adding counter increment and check operations.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Negligible**: Two integer operations per skip are trivial compared to buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations and character comparisons[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only checked when [0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m, not on every character[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Alternative Approaches Considered and Rejected[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Modifying the do-while loop structure**: Would require extensive refactoring [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand risk breaking existing functionality.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Adding timeout mechanism**: Would require threading or timer infrastructure, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madding complexity.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Pre-scanning for excessive whitespace**: Would require an extra pass through [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer, impacting performance for all fonts.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Removing whitespace skipping**: Would break legitimate fonts that use [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout occurring during PDF text extraction, with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe main thread stuck in `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method after running for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproximately [0m[1;36m28[0m[39m seconds. A patch was applied to the `Type1Lexer.java` file that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madds a counter to limit consecutive whitespace or NULL byte skips to [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations, throwing a `DamagedFontException` when exceeded. However, after [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the timeout issue persists with the main thread now appearing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto be stuck in `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue manifests as a libFuzzer timeout with the following key [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacteristics:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Thread State**: The main thread [0m[1;39m([0m[33mtid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x000056487bba6b70[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is in RUNNABLE state,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsuming significant CPU time [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m26660.[0m[39m43ms over [0m[1;36m28.[0m[39m61s elapsed time[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Stack Trace Location**: The thread is stuck at:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.runtime.TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mNative Method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Lexer.jav[0m[1;92ma:247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Lexer.jav[0m[1;92ma:75[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:643[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Call Chain**: The issue originates from PDF processing:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mPDFTextStripper.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → Font loading → Type1 font parsing → Lexer token [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Symptoms**: The RUNNABLE state combined with high CPU usage suggests an [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite or extremely long-running loop rather than a deadlock or blocking [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperation.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies `org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java` with the following [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Added constant**: `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS = [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m52[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Modified `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** starting at line [0m[1;36m119[0m[39m:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a counter variable `consecutiveSkips` initialized to [0m[1;36m0[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added increment logic when whitespace is encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m202[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added increment logic when NULL bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both increment locations include a check: if `consecutiveSkips > [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS`, throw a `DamagedFontException` with a descriptive message[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Implementation specifics**:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The counter tracks consecutive skip operations in the do-while loop[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When the threshold is exceeded, an exception is thrown indicating [0m[32m"Excessive [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mwhitespace or NULL bytes at position"[0m[39m with the current buffer position[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The counter is not reset when non-skip characters are encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich would[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappen when `skip = false`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Observations[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the timeout still occurs with these notable differences:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Stack Trace Change**: The stuck location shifted from:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before: `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Lexer.jav[0m[1;92ma:247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After: `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:640[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Similar Runtime Characteristics**:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - CPU time: [0m[1;36m26628.[0m[39m46ms [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcompared to [0m[1;36m26660.[0m[39m43ms before[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Call Stack**: The stack trace now shows:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   at [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This indicates the timeout moved from the lexer to the parser level.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m and surrounding code should be examined for potential infinite loops[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relationship between this method and the lexer should be analyzed[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Investigate what operations at line [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m could cause extended execution time[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - While the patch addresses consecutive skips, the original issue at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay involve other looping conditions[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The complete logic of the do-while loop and all conditions that set `skip = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrue` should be reviewed[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch only addresses whitespace and NULL bytes, but other characters or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions might cause similar issues[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **ByteBuffer operations**: [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer position tracking and advancement logic should be examined[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m always advances and cannot get stuck[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Type1Parser-Lexer interaction**: [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine how `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls the lexer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Investigate whether malformed input can cause the parser to repeatedly request[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens without making progress[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Input validation**: [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer-generated input that triggers this timeout should be analyzed if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consider what types of malformed Type1 font data could cause these [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpathological behaviors[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Native callback overhead**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The presence of `TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt` in both stack [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraces suggests fuzzing instrumentation may be amplifying the performance issue[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consider whether the actual issue is a large number of comparisons rather than[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man infinite loop[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
