[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**The Critical Flaw in the Previous Patch:**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe last patch attempt added a `consecutiveSkips` counter inside the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod, but based on the code structure and the patch description, the counter [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappears to be initialized at line [0m[1;36m119[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside the method but within the do-while [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop scope starting at line [0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This means the counter gets reset on each [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration of the outer do-while loop, preventing it from accumulating properly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross iterations.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Root Cause:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs in `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when processing a malformed font [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith an extremely long sequence of whitespace or NULL bytes. The do-while loop [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continues while `[0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`, and when the buffer contains[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmillions of consecutive skip characters, each character is processed individually, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing excessive CPU consumption and eventual timeout.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why Parser Loop Patches Don't Help:**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patches to `Type1Parser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39madding iteration counters to the search loops[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtreat the symptom, not the cause. These counters only limit how many times the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser loops call `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, but if a single `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call hangs [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinitely in `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, the parser counters never get incremented.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Primary Fix: Correct the Counter Placement in [0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java`**[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must ensure the `consecutiveSkips` counter is:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initialized BEFORE the do-while loop** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore line [0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - not at line [0m[1;36m119[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the previous patch placed it[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Never reset within the loop** - it must accumulate across all outer do-while [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Incremented at every skip character encounter** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m204[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Checked immediately after increment** to throw `DamagedFontException` when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceeded[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation approach:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Move the `consecutiveSkips` counter initialization to line [0m[1;36m118[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mright after the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod signature, before any loop logic[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS` constant definition [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready added in previous [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensure counter increments occur at lines [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `[0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` is set[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add exception throwing logic immediately after each increment[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Remove the reset of the counter that might have been in the previous patch[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Secondary Fix: Maintain Type1Parser Iteration Limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDefensive Programming[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java`**[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhile the primary issue is in the lexer, the parser-level iteration limits should [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe retained as a secondary defense layer, but with adjustments:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Keep the `MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS` constant** as defined in the previous patch[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Retain iteration counters** in all three search loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m556[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m568[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Adjust the counter logic** to ensure they're incremented correctly in each [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop iteration[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Add null checks** where needed [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready in previous patch at encoding search[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese parser limits serve as a backup in case the lexer fix misses edge cases, but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey won't solve the core problem alone.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Detailed Implementation Steps[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Fix [0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Counter Placement[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStarting from the **initial codebase** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot the patched version[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Keep the `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS = [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m` constant added by the previous patch[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken prevToken[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method structure:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private Token [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken prevToken[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       int consecutiveSkips = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m MUST be here, line [0m[1;36m118[0m[39m, BEFORE boolean skip;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       boolean skip;               [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m line [0m[1;36m119[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       do                          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m line [0m[1;36m120[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           skip = false;           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m line [0m[1;36m122[0m[39m - DO NOT reset consecutiveSkips here[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m existing code [0m[33m...[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return null;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. At line [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhitespace check[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, modify to:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCharacter.isWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       skip = true;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       consecutiveSkips++;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkips > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"Excessive whitespace or NULL bytes [0m[32m([0m[32m>"[0m[39m + MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. At line [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL byte check[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, modify to:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"NULL byte in font, skipped"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       skip = true;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       consecutiveSkips++;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkips > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"Excessive whitespace or NULL bytes [0m[32m([0m[32m>"[0m[39m + MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Reapply Type1Parser Limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom previous patch[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReapply the parser-level limits from the previous patch to `Type1Parser.java`:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Keep the `MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m` constant[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Reapply the encoding search iteration limit [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m235[0m[39m in patched version[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Reapply the Private token search iteration limit [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m567[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m585[0m[39m in patched [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversion[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Note: The CharStrings search loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was NOT patched previously, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut should be considered for consistency[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, adjust the logic to ensure:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Counters are incremented at the start of each loop iteration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot just on token [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madvance[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Exception messages are consistent[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Null checks are properly placed[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses Root Cause**: Fixes the actual infinite loop location in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` where excessive skip characters cause timeout[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes**: Only modifies the counter placement and increment [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic, preserving all existing functionality[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Follows Codebase Patterns**: Similar to `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readStringNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses accumulated counters across loop iterations[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Reasonable Limits**: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive whitespace/NULL bytes is far more than[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many legitimate font would contain[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Parser-level limits provide backup protection[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **No Functional Changes**: The lexer still processes characters the same way, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjust with a safety limit[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Same Token Generation**: All token types and parsing logic remain unchanged[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Maintains API Compatibility**: Method signatures and public interfaces [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Exception Handling**: Uses existing `DamagedFontException` already in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Logging Preserved**: Keeps the existing LOG.warn for NULL bytes[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report Issues[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents Timeout**: The counter limit stops processing before timeout occurs[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Targets Correct Location**: Fixes `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdo-while[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where stack trace shows the issue[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Handles Malformed Input**: Protects against malicious/damaged fonts with [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive padding[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Allows Fuzzing to Continue**: Throws proper exception instead of hanging, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mletting fuzzer test other inputs[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[3;91mFalse[0m[39m Positives**: Legitimate fonts with unusual whitespace patterns might [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger the limit[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive skip characters is extremely high; [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate fonts won't hit this[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Error Messages**: Users might see `DamagedFontException` for fonts that [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreviously [0m[1;39m([0m[39mslowly[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m worked[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: These fonts are already problematic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtaking too long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; fast [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure is better than timeout[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance Impact**: Adding counter increments and checks[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Minimal - only two integer increments and comparisons per skip[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacter[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Test Compatibility**: Existing tests should pass as they use well-formed fonts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: No test modifications needed; malformed test fonts should [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly fail now[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach mirrors existing patterns:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readStringNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1443[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1461[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses accumulated counter [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross loop iterations with `[0m[1;35mbuffer.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_LENGTH_LONG` check[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **PfbParser.MAX_LENGTH** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m71[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Defines reasonable limits for font [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **BaseParser thresholds** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m66[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses constants like [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`OBJECT_NUMBER_THRESHOLD` to prevent excessive processing[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll these examples show that PDFBox already uses iteration/accumulation limits to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent hangs - this fix applies the same pattern consistently.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
